summaries.short: Judd enlists Ryan to charm an intimidating, super-wealthy passenger. Rav deals with media outrage.
summaries.full: Judd enlists Ryan to help charm Harrison Aimes, an uber-wealthy passenger who has a strange effect on Judd. Meanwhile, the passengers become transfixed by a divine image circling the ship and Rav deals with the fallout when the ship’s moral quandary hits the media.

summaries.short: Karen collects non-essential items to jettison as frenzied passengers develop a conspiracy theory.
summaries.full: While Karen oversees an effort to jettison non-essential passenger items, Billie tries to teach an inattentive Ryan how to dock the ship. Matt learns of Judd's plan to make the "ultimate sacrifice" by returning to Earth. Meanwhile, the passengers suspect all is not as it seems with the journey.

summaries.short: Ryan and Billie try to find the source of an incessant beeping. Rav appeals to the President for rescue funds.
summaries.full: As Avenue 5 celebrates the birth of a space baby, Ryan and Billie try to identify the source of an incessant beeping, and Judd shares his latest grand idea at Karen's passenger-crew liaison meeting. In the nation's capital, Rav appeals to the President for rescue funds but, in exchange, is faced with an ethical dilemma.

summaries.short: Season One Finale. Matt takes extreme measures to quiet a guilty conscience, and a seat on a rescue shuttle sends the ship into chaos.
summaries.full: Season One Finale. A search party commences for Matt, who's in hiding with a guilty conscience – and the airlock codes. Iris questions Karen about her rumored affair with Ryan. Rav seeks an apology from Judd for ruining her life, as chaos ensues when a seat on a rescue shuttle suddenly becomes available.
